Brezhev era when he reined the troonier earlier stuff in and turned the USSR into something approximating a functional state. Actually ideology in 60s USSR was lead by the Second Secretary (whose title meant more like a "Secretary of Ideology") who in that era was Mikhail Suslov.

Suslov was like a shadow president of the USSR and a lot of figures like Andropov were his personal proteges. He started occupying top positions under Stalin and was never removed from power until his death, the only one from that era left. You can tell he was a ruthless guy.
A lot of this was just what they had to do to fight WW2 without people switching to the other side, demoralization makes less sense when you're trying to get people to die fighting Germans
